&lt;h2 id="about-this-session">About this session&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>We will be presenting a demo of our new restructured DSOMM application and the ways in which you can utilize it to elevate you DevSecOps game.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>In this presentation we plan to go in depth, explaining how you can use the new dashboard to assess your team&amp;rsquo;s or organization&amp;rsquo;s application security maturity&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="reference">Reference&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>In case you unfamiliar with OWASP DSOMM, please watch an already &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?app=desktop&amp;amp;v=lLMLGIzl56M">recorded session&lt;/a> where we explain the use of DSOMM.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Permission Models As Code - Securing the Entire Stack</title><link>https://open-security-summit.org/sessions/2022/mini-summits/sep/devsecops/permission-models-as-code-securing-the-entire-stack/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://open-security-summit.org/sessions/2022/mini-summits/sep/devsecops/permission-models-as-code-securing-the-entire-stack/</guid><description>&lt;h3 id="session-slides">Session slides&lt;/h3>
