&lt;h2 id="about-this-session">About this session&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>In this presentation, we will discuss a number of topics that will provide an insight into how permission models as code can be used to secure products from top to bottom - from infrastructure up to the application layer.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The following topics will be discussed:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Why permissions are hard to build and maintain&lt;/li>
&lt;li>The different options for permission models&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Policy as Code&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Generating policy as code (Rego) - with Permit.io&amp;rsquo;s low-code policy editor&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Applying policies to Kubernetes infrastructure&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Applying policies to the application layer&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
